 (26,'00270','Cysteine and methionine metabolism','Cysteine and methionine are sulfur-containing amino acids. Cysteine is synthesized from serine through different pathways in different organism groups. In bacteria and plants, cysteine is converted from serine (via acetylserine) by transfer of hydrogen sulfide [MD:M00021]. In animals, methionine-derived homocysteine is used as sulfur source and its condensation product with serine (cystathionine) is converted to cysteine [MD:M00338]. Cysteine is metabolized to pyruvate in multiple routes. Methionine is an essential amino acid, which animals cannot synthesize. In bacteria and plants, methionine is synthesized from aspartate [MD:M00017]. S-Adenosylmethionine (SAM), synthesized from methionine and ATP, is a methyl group donor in many important transfer reactions including DNA methylation for regulation of gene expression. SAM may also be used to regenerate methionine in the methionine salvage pathway [MD:M00034].','Metabolism; Amino acid metabolism','Cysteine and methionine metabolism','Methionine biosynthesis, apartate => homoserine => methionine [PATH:map00270], Cysteine biosynthesis, serine => cysteine [PATH:map00270], Methionine salvage pathway [PATH:map00270], Methionine degradation [PATH:map00270], Cysteine biosynthesis, homocysteine + serine => cysteine [PATH:map00270], Ethylene biosynthesis, methionine => ethylene [PATH:map00270], Cysteine biosynthesis, methionine => cysteine [PATH:map00270]','Cystathioninuria, Homocystinuria, Hypermethioninemia, Snyder-Robinson syndrome, Methylcobalamin deficiency type G, Tatton-Brown-Rahman syndrome','GO: 0006534 0006555','ko00270','list(REFERENCE = "PMID:15102328", AUTHORS = "Sekowska A, Denervaud V, Ashida H, Michoud K, Haas D, Yokota A, Danchin A", TITLE = "Bacterial variations on the methionine salvage pathway.", JOURNAL = c("BMC Microbiol 4:9 (2004)", "DOI:10.1186/1471-2180-4-9")), list(REFERENCE = "PMID:14551435", AUTHORS = "Ashida H, Saito Y, Kojima C, Kobayashi K, Oga